{
  "doc_id": "8932",
  "text": "The questionnaire data were analysed principally by means of descriptive statistics. The analysis of the transcribed focus group proceedings used the following steps: [CITATION_1] 1 Identifying the key areas (identifying the broad topics and ideas that emerged from the data). 2 Unitising the data (identifying specific quotations that express informants' perceptions and feelings, and that can subsequently be used to define categories). 3 Allocating the units (all units identified in the previous step were grouped into homogeneous categories; these categories were not predetermined, but were generated inductively from the data). 4 Negotiating categories (categories were reviewed and joined or subdivided and new categories were created, as appropriate). 5 Identifying themes (the revised categories and supporting units were re-examined and refined and restated as themes).",
